         <t:abstract>
            <t:p>There are four anaphoras known under the name of Gregory: <t:ref type="work" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT2040Naakkw">Anaphora of St
                                                  Gregory of Nyssa</t:ref>, <t:ref type="work" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT2038Naakkw">The Second Anaphora
                                                  of St Gregory</t:ref>,
            <t:ref type="work" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT2034Naakkw">Anaphora of Our Lady
                                                  Mary by Gregory</t:ref> and <t:ref type="work" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT2037Naakkw">Anaphora of Our Lady
                                                  Mary by Gregory or Nathaniel element TEI with id LIT2037Naakkw</t:ref>. They can be distinguished only by their incipit, content and use, as they
            are indiscriminately ascribed to <t:persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS4823Gregory">Gregory of Neocaesarea</t:persName>,
            <t:persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS4822Gregory">Gregory of Nazianzos</t:persName>, <t:persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS4824Gregory">Gregory of Nyssa</t:persName> and <t:persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS4825Gregory">Gregory the Illuminator</t:persName>.</t:p>
         </t:abstract>
